# Testing & Quality Rules

## Before Submitting
- Run `npm run typecheck` and `npm run lint` — both must pass with zero errors
- Manually verify the feature works end-to-end in the browser

## Code Quality
- All exported functions must have a JSDoc comment explaining purpose and parameters
- No magic numbers — extract named constants with UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Maximum function length: 40 lines. Extract helpers if longer.
- Prefer early returns over nested conditionals

## Accessibility
- All images must have meaningful `alt` text (not empty string unless decorative)
- All buttons must have accessible labels (via text content or `aria-label`)
- Color must not be the only indicator of state — include text or icons alongside color changes
